The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques for part-of-speech (POS) tagging of code-mixed Indian social media text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, such as distributed representations and log-linear models, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of feature extraction, which is a common topic in sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper mentions the use of word2vec, which is a popular technique in sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
